data.name: Ascii Art Generator
data.description:

It gets an image, and returns a string representing the image. What's preloaded?

1. const image1={data-uri} //image 1 2. const image2={data-uri} //image 2 3. const Canvas = require('canvas') 4. const Image = Canvas.Image 5. const width=64, height=64 (the output will always be 64x64 pixels, and the images will always be square) And most importantly: 5. 
const intensity = " .:-=+*#%@" //a string of 10 characters representing different intensity levels:
intensity[0]=" " (space) represents a completely white (blank) pixel 
intensity[9]="@" (at) represents a completely black (full) pixel 
and ofcourse everything in between.
6. 

var draw = function (original,ascii) {} //accepts the original image (i.e. image1) and your generated string.
It prints the result to the console (shows the original, and your version)

Specifications:

You will convert every pixel into a character. RGB values should be summed, and then normalized (round any decimals) to the range of intensities (0-9). Alpha value should be ignored.

Good luck!

p.s.

If you found any bugs please let me know. If your image looks more or less like the expected result, yet you failed the test, it's important that I'll know about it, because there could be small variations that I should be able to account for. Thanks!!
